<TITLE> RU Shibir leader arrested </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 25 (bdnews24.com)  RAB arrested Rajshahi University Shibir leader Shamsul Alam Golap, an accused in Faruk Hosain murder case, at Bhuapur in Tangail. The president of RU Islami Chhatra Shibir unit was arrested at around 2 am on Thursday, Lt Col Ziaul Ahsan, commander of RAB's intelligence unit told bdnews24.com. Golap has been a fugitive since the killing of RU's Chhatra League activist Faruk Hossain in February. Police so far arrested hundreds of Shibir activists after the killing of Faruk during violence with the student wing of Jamaat-e-Islami Bangladesh on Feb 8. 
